data.description: This single-story home offers several upgrades and features that were implemented before builders started reducing the quality of materials. Here is a breakdown of the notable aspects of the property:  Ceramic Tile Floors: The home features ceramic tile floors, which are known for their durability, easy maintenance, and aesthetic appeal. This home is constructed with stone/brick on all four sides. This type of construction adds visual appeal, provides better insulation, and offers increased durability and longevity compared to other materials.  Tilt-Out Windows: The windows in this home are designed to tilt out, allowing for easier cleaning and maintenance. Tilt-out windows provide convenient access to both sides of the glass, making them a practical choice for homeowners.  Higher Ceilings: The home boasts higher ceilings, which can create a sense of spaciousness and openness. Higher ceilings also allow for better airflow and natural light distribution, contributing to a more comfortable living environment.  Covered Patio: The property includes a covered patio, which is a valuable outdoor space for relaxation, entertaining guests, or enjoying meals outdoors. The covered patio provides shade and protection from the elements, allowing you to make use of the outdoor area throughout the year.  In addition to these features, the home has three bedrooms and two full bathrooms. The owner's suite, located at the back of the home, offers a full bathroom and a large walk-in closet. The presence of a formal dining room or optional flex room adds versatility to the layout, providing extra space that can be used according to your needs.    Overall, this home stands out for its upgraded features and materials, offering a combination of functionality, durability, and aesthetic appeal.
